videos.description: Michigan's Wilton Speight finishes perfect first drive with a 43-yard pass to Kekoa Crawford for a touchdown.
videos.headline: Michigan strikes first with TD

videos.description: Michigan's Tyree Kinnel capitalizes on the high throw by Cincinnati's Hayden Moore for the pick-six.
videos.headline: Michigan's defense puts points on the board with pick-six

videos.description: Cincinnati makes the most of its special teams by recovering a Michigan fumble during a punt.
videos.headline: Cincinnati gets lucky with fumble recovery

videos.description: Cincinnati puts an exclamation mark on the drive after the fumble recovery as Mike Boone powers through the line for a rushing TD to cut Michigan's lead to 14-7.
videos.headline: Cincinnati surges into the end zone

videos.description: Michigan's Donovan Peoples-Jones runs the jet sweep with success for 44 yards and a first down to end the first quarter against Cincinnati.
videos.headline: Michigan runs out the first quarter with big run

videos.description: Michigan runs the jet sweep unsuccessfully as the Wolverines fumble the ball in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Cincinnati's defense forces another turnover

videos.description: Cincinnati coach Luke Fickell explains how the Bearcats have managed to keep the game close with Michigan in the first half.
videos.headline: Fickell happy to keep it close with Michigan

videos.description: Cincinnati's Hayden Moore keeps it himself to run for 46 yards to set up the Bearcats with great field position.
videos.headline: Cincinnati's Moore runs for huge gain

videos.description: Cincinnati's Hayden Moore finds Kahlil Lewis for the 10-yard touchdown catch to keep pull the Bearcats into one score of the Wolverines.
videos.headline: Cincinnati cuts into Michigan's lead

videos.description: Michigan's Wilton Speight finds Grant Perry for the 33-yard touchdown pass.
videos.headline: Perry dives in the end zone for Michigan TD

videos.description: Michigan's Ty Isaac breaks off a run for 53 yards to help spark the Wolverines' offense.
videos.headline: Isaac's huge run sets up Wolverines

videos.description: As the play clock winds down, Cincinnati snaps the ball to James Smith, who is not ready, Smith is forced to slap the ball out of the back of the end zone.
videos.headline: Cincinnati snaps the ball without warning

videos.description: Cincinnati's Hayden Moore throws his second pick-six of the game as Michigan extends its lead against the Bearcats.
videos.headline: Michigan gets second pick-six

videos.description: Brock Huard and Bob Wischusen dig into Michigan's strong defensive performance and Allison Williams talks to defensive lineman Rashan Gray about leading the defense to victory in the 36-14 win over Cincinnati.
videos.headline: Michigan's defense strong against Cincinnati

videos.description: Michigan coach Jim Harbaugh says while his age and experience make him impervious to butterflies during games, he's glad his young players had a chance to work through that against Cincinnati.
